<div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64874486"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64874486,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;mikepaganucci&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Mike Paganucci&quot;}"></div><a name="star1"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star2" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://mikepaganucci.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=MikePaganucci4F1A3621-BC3D-8B26-966E-765BB6FB82FC.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://mikepaganucci.newsvine.com/">Mike Paganucci</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64874486" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Republicans are begging for the Occupy movement to regroup. This is a big issue for students and if the Republicans block the bill, it may be the catalyst to bring out student protests again. I hope the Republicans do block the bill so that students can mobilize for this bill, the Occupy movement and the elections. It would do for the Dems what they are unable to do--communicate an effective message to the whole middle class in all states including the red ones. A galvanized Occupy movement would be a Republican nightmare even in safe states and districts.</p></div>
