<span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64879222" title="Link to this comment">#4.1</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 5:05 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64877962"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64877962,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;deb3596991&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Deb-3596991&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://deb3596991.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://deb3596991.newsvine.com/">Deb-3596991</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64877962" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>This whole Republican dark agenda is so ridiculous that it isn&rsquo;t even funny anymore. They basically want to get rid of anything that helps the middle class and poor people so everyone has to fend for himself or herself. They want everyone to carry their own gun for protection as they reduce law enforcement. They want to get rid of any environmental protection regulation we have so everyone can be subject to a real wasteland of pollution and contamination. And than when people start becoming sick, don&rsquo;t waste your time going to a hospital, because you will have no coverage to pay for it. But now that everyone is getting sick let&rsquo;s make sure we take away any woman&rsquo;s rights and keep her barefoot and pregnant in poverty, because we have to replace those people that are dying by the droves. We must also have no education for the average person either, since the people must stay illiterate and ignorant to everything that has been done to them. Who would even want to live in such a world like this, are these Republicans literally that insane, because to me this is a world that is just not worth living in. </p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64877962,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;deb3596991&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64877962" title="Link to this comment">#5</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 4:31 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64879253"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64879253,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;juergenh&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;JuergenH&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://juergenh.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://juergenh.newsvine.com/">JuergenH</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64879253" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>College education should be free, as in other industrialized countries. How to pay for it? Raise the effective tax rate on high incomes, not to 33% or whatever it was before the Bush tax cuts but to 40 or 50%.</p></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64879253,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;juergenh&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64879253" title="Link to this comment">#6</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 5:06 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c64881723"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64881723,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;crackheadawards&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Crackhead Awards&quot;}"></div><a name="star6"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star7" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://crackheadawards.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=crackheadawards0FB1C990-46E1-7BC7-5FED-F27987334B67.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://crackheadawards.newsvine.com/">Crackhead Awards</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64881723" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Every other country has done the math, and those that subsidize education have a better economy.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64881723,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;crackheadawards&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">5 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64881723" title="Link to this comment">#6.1</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 6:06 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c64882511"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64882511,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;skiphoffman&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;skip hoffman&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/">skip hoffman</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64882511" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Are some of the countries that have free college education in the EU mess like Greece, Spain and Italy? I am all for higher education for all, but we have to find a balance between that and other programs...and that would of course include higher taxes as part of it. When I decided to go to college I never once thought of it as a right and I did not expect to get outright $$ for it. I just am not wired that way. I spent 5 years in the Navy, got out and used my GI bill. Since that didn't really cover all of it I worked 20-30 hours a week on campus and stayed in the Naval Reserves. I am not expecting a pat on the back for this.. it's just that I believed I had to work and earn my degree. I guess a little different and do not look at the Federal or State or local governments for aid in a category like college. I may be totally wrong, but that's how I thought about it and still do now. I honestly do no remember my parent's generation talking about grants and low interest loans to go to school. Yes, there was a big influx of college students as a result of the wars (GI Bill), but I did get the impression (at least from the families I lived around as a Navy brat) that it was something that people had to work hard for - some harder than others.</p>
<p>I don't know...I'm just thinking about how the term entitlement has become more and more of a prominent term in today's world. And I just think that a college education would fall into a "want" type of aid rather than a "need" type of aid (food stamps, unemployment, etc) . Now if we have $$ left over after all the "need" entitlements are taken care of, then I am all for MORE college grants and low interest loans. But for now, we just can't keep overspending in an insanely excessive amount.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64882511,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;skiphoffman&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64882511" title="Link to this comment">#6.2</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 6:30 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c64889574"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64889574,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;themouzer&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;The Mouzer&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://themouzer.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=TheMouzerDFA29372-3A4B-252C-5E67-A1BA5957C69A.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://themouzer.newsvine.com/">The Mouzer</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64889574" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><blockquote>
<p>I spent 5 years in the Navy, got out and used my GI bill</p>
<p>I guess a little different and do not look at the Federal or State or local governments for aid in a category like college</p>
</blockquote>
<p>....keep your government hands off of my GI bill. </p>
<p>Seriously skip?  You've got to be kidding me</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I'm just thinking about how the term entitlement has become more and more of a prominent term in today's world</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Because the Republican messaging machine keeps repeating this term over and over again and then, for whatever reason, you continuously pick up on it and then you too repeat the term over and over again (and yes I realize you're not a Republican so do not bother pointing that out- my point is you are regurgitating the same statement over again and then using post hoc reasoning to conclude why).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>And I just think that a college education would fall into a "want" type of aid rather than a "need" type of aid</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Absolutely no one is arguing w/ this</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>But for now, we just can't keep overspending in an insanely excessive amount</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Repeat this w/ me skip:  paying money up front for college costs less money in the long term. </p>
<p>If you take government loans and grants out of college education you are going to see a <em>massive </em>reduction in the amount of income the middle class makes, a massive reduction in the amount of wealthy people that exist in this country, a massive reduction in overall GDP, and a massive reduction in the long-term employment rate.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64889574,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;themouzer&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64889574" title="Link to this comment">#6.3</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 10:24 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c64890854"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64890854,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;meddlingmonk&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;MeddlingMonk&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://meddlingmonk.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=meddlingmonk23DE183B-C814-28CA-A930-EBE95749D42A.uncropped.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://meddlingmonk.newsvine.com/">MeddlingMonk</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64890854" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Oh, God.</p>
<p>***Bangs head into wall, realizes that's a stupid thing to do, and bangs skip's head into the wall instead.***</p>
