<p>'m just thinking about how the term entitlement has become more and more of a prominent term in today's world</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I just want to point this out.  This particular conversation was started by<a href="http://juergenh.newsvine.com/"> JuergenH</a> who did not mention entitlements.</p>
<p>Then <a href="http://crackheadawards.newsvine.com/">Crackhead Awards</a> responded who also did not mention entitlements.</p>
<p>Then <a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/?__utma=238145375.1443261404.1334511143.1334966329.1334973686.39&amp;__utmb=238145375.41.10.1334973686&amp;__utmc=238145375&amp;__utmx=-&amp;__utmz=238145375.1334511143.1.1.utmcsr=%28direct%29%7Cutmccn=%28direct%29%7Cutmcmd=%28none%29%7Cutmctr=%28not%20provided%29&amp;__utmv=238145375.%7C8=Earned%20By=msnbc%7Ccover=1&amp;__utmk=27354879">skip hoffman</a> responded who mentioned entitlements.</p>
<p>Then I responded and my only mention of entitlements was in pointing out the post hoc reasoning and in re-quoting skip.</p>
<p>Then <a href="http://meddlingmonk.newsvine.com/">MeddlingMonk</a> responds and did not mention entitlements.</p>
<p>The only people calling student loans entitlements are, apparently, those who do not see student loans are prudent investments.  Which OK if you don't like them then you are certainly at liberty to make your case.  But I just wanted to point out that it's only <em>one </em>segment who are talking about 'entitlements.'  So stating that 'entitlements' keep coming up in conversation....well, like I said, that's some really weird logic there.</p>
<p><a href="http://juergenh.newsvine.com/"> </a></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64891114,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;themouzer&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64891114" title="Link to this comment">#6.5</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 11:16 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c64891454"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64891454,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;skiphoffman&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;skip hoffman&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/">skip hoffman</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64891454" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Fair point Mouzer. Like i said in my first post I may be wrong :). But what would a federal grant be called? Just a grant. It is money given and no repayment required.</p>
<p>I did chuckle on your "keep you government hands off my GI Bill" - I really did. I do see how hypocritical it looks. But I do see the GI Bill as part of the pay and benefits of serving in the military - you had to serve at least 6 months on active duty to get it, unlike a federal college grant that requires no such service.</p>
<p>As I stated also earlier I am all for aid for college...I just look at it as a lower priority than other much needed programs. I have brought up the spending and debt issues our country has many times here (probably too much for some here) but I can not believe that most folks here barely mention the fact that we continually spend more than we take in - for so many straight years that it is becoming a habit. That is all I guess I was trying to get across. And yes I do believe in more taxes - but also a little less spending too.</p>
<p>I am proud that I worked my ass off to get my degree. I left home at 17 and joined the military for that very reason. I may have misspoken (misposted??) with the word entitlement I guess. I was trying to express my opinion that it seems that it is a given that the government will give you money for a college degree - everytime. Last week or so I heard a piece on the radio about 4 million trade jobs go unfilled because young people do not want to learn a trade skill, and the funny thing is most of the trade schools are paid for by unions and similar private concerns. The average pay of these trade skilled jobs are $60,000 too. Maybe this can solve some of this middle class issue you speak of my friend Mouzer :)</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64891454,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;skiphoffman&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64891454" title="Link to this comment">#6.6</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 11:37 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c64891740"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64891740,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;skiphoffman&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;skip hoffman&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/">skip hoffman</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64891740" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Oh and I forgot Mouzer... you're right no one mention the <em>word </em>entitlement except me.</p>
<p>Jurgen mentioned free</p>
<p>Crackhead mentioned subsidized</p>
<p>So free or subsidized college is not an entitlement. Just want to make sure I got that right :).</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64891740,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;skiphoffman&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64891740" title="Link to this comment">#6.7</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 11:53 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c64891941"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64891941,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;themouzer&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;The Mouzer&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://themouzer.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=TheMouzerDFA29372-3A4B-252C-5E67-A1BA5957C69A.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://themouzer.newsvine.com/">The Mouzer</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64891941" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><blockquote>
<p>But what would a federal grant be called? Just a grant. It is money given and no repayment required.</p>
<p>unlike a federal college grant that requires no such service.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The GI bill is a grant that is given out to people who have served in the US military.  And yes I would agree that it's a general benefit given to you for your service.  I just thought the way you worded it came across as funny- it sounded like you were saying you didn't receive government benefits while simultaneously talking about your GI bill.  I wouldn't care either way- I believe that you should receive government benefits, <em>especially </em>if you worked for the government (which you did).  But it was just one of those double-take moments from how you worded it.</p>
<p>Just as the GI bill requires that you meet the veteran/active duty status in order to receive it so too do the non-military based grants given by the federal government have strict requirements that you must meet and maintain.  Federal grants have requirements that must be met to qualify such as income restrictions, family college status (so if you aren't the first in your family to go to college there are certain grants you automatically don't qualify for), or academic grants.  Academic grants, as an example, require that you have a certain GPA and that you maintain that GPA.  Failure to maintain the GPA will result in you losing your grant money <em>and </em>if you do not meet those requirements prior to applying you will also be denied.</p>
<p>Some grants will make you pay if you do not maintain your GPA since the contract you make states that you <em>must </em>keep your grades above average.  Grants operate differently than federal loans.  A grant- w/ some exceptions- does not have to be paid back.  As I said sometimes they will make you pay it back if it's found out that you abused the grant (like by not keeping your GPA up), but assuming you don't violate the contract a grant is something you don't have to pay back.  A loan, however, from the federal government works <strong>exactly </strong>like a private loan w/ the exception of a sub-market level low rate.  A regular student loan has anywhere from a 10-30% interest rate.  A federal loan usually has anywhere from a 1%-4% interest rate.  Both must be paid off over time.  The government, for the record, makes a profit off programs like FAFSA.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I just look at it as a lower priority than other much needed programs</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I am not sure anyone is disagreeing w/ you on this.  The only thing I would add, however, is that we have a serious problem of income inequality and in particular we have a problem w/ too many people making too little money.  Education is pretty much the only way to increase the income that individuals make.  This also, ftr, increases the amount of money that they can pay in taxes which then goes on to help w/ the debt.  But I would grant you that it's far more important to make sure someone is fed and clothed than to make sure someone goes to school.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I was trying to express my opinion that it seems that it is a given that  the government will give you money for a college degree - everytime</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is far more sensible to state ;-)  I suppose I was being a bit too sarcastic towards you, so I apologize.  Sometimes I forget that people cannot hear the inflection w/ which you speak through the Internets.</p>
<p>I guess to some extent people do believe that they will be given some federal money and to another extent they do not.  Federal loans do not pay 100% of your college tuition rate.  Federal loans and public grants usually only equate to about a third of your total tuition costs.  Most college students then have to work and take out a private loan to finish off the remaining 2/3's <em>or </em>they have to use scholarships and private grants.  I do not personally know of a single person who has gone to college in modern America who has not had to take out <em>some </em>type of loan from the private sector or who hasn't had to jump through hoops in order to get enough grant/scholarship money from the private sector so as to not have to take out private loans.</p>
<p>When I say jump through hoops I mean I literally knew a person who applied for the Aryan Race Scholarship (yes such a thing exists) because it would offer him 600$ a semester to pay for tuition.</p>
<p>I also know a person who donated an ovary to pay for college tuition (however in fairness to her this was to put her through medical school and medical school is abnormally expensive (like 150-200,000$)).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Last week or so I heard a piece on the radio about 4 million trade jobs  go unfilled because young people do not want to learn a trade skill, and  the funny thing is most of the trade schools are paid for by unions and  similar private concerns</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That is disturbing.  I'd like to know more about that if you can find any information on it.  My understanding is that a trade job requires that you get an apprenticeship.  I have heard that in states like Iowa and Pennsylvania they still do apprenticeships...but most places don't do that.  So I'm not sure how you'd get training for a trade job.  Trade schools don't even exist in every state or every city any more.  Community colleges usually will help you get a certificate or AA degree in in-demand fields or fields that require that you have specific training (like, for instance, Denver Automotive and Diesel College (my best friends sister was formerly married to a man who went there and got trained as an airplane mechanic....yeah he got a union job almost immediately and makes bank like 80k/yr now)).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>So free or subsidized college is not an entitlement</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Your complaint initially was that you heard the <em>word </em>entitlement too often.  I was pointing out that this was silly reasoning.  Your revised statement (in your rebuttal post) makes far more sense.  I will gladly retract my previous statement about this since I was fixated on the dynamics of your language use rather than the meaning.  I honestly had no idea what it was that you were talking about at the time- w/ your revised statement I feel that I have now connected the dots.  Redacted =)</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64891941,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;themouzer&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64891941" title="Link to this comment">#6.8</a> - Sat Apr 21, 2012 12:06 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c64892203"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64892203,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;skiphoffman&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;skip hoffman&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://skiphoffman.newsvine.com/">skip hoffman</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64892203" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I like debating with you Mouzer :). And to be fair, yes there are requirements to get federal grants so I guess they are just not throwing $$ at folks.</p>
<p>I think I heard the trade school piece on "The Osgood Minute" which I hear on WBBM AM newsradio in the mornings on the way to work. I don't remember the piece verbatum, but it may have been about the apprentiships you mentioned as well as some trade schools. I did learn a trade myself in the service - although it was a very specialized skill. I started out working on flight simulators which required a working knowledge of electonics, hydraulics and basic flight training. A couple of my fellow "shipmates" did get pretty good paying jobs with airlines working on their simulators after their hitch. For me, the Navy in their infinite wisdom (pun intended) switched me over to Naval Intelligence after a few years (because they discontinued our rate /speciality and civilianized it). That was a bit more interesting...</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64892203,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;skiphoffman&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64892203" title="Link to this comment">#6.9</a> - Sat Apr 21, 2012 12:24 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64879872"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64879872,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jjffmm&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;JJFFMM&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://jjffmm.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://jjffmm.newsvine.com/">JJFFMM</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64879872" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Well all I can say is the complete detachment of financial considerations from the people who are linked to these financial considerations is a new and weird turn of affairs in the world.</p>
<p>I was reading in the NYT today that if the Socialists win in France then the (democratically elected) government will have to face off against what truly governs the world: "the markets.' The thesis in the article is that if Sarkozy wins there will be more austerity to satisfy "the markets" but less austerity if Hollande wins, deferring the gratification of "the markets" for some years down the road.</p>
<p>"The markets" are the financial markets who long ago severed all relationship to the people on which these "markets" are ultimately based. It's almost like the pre-revolutionary aristocracy in France, wanting nothing more than to distance itself as much as possible from "the rabble." Who were, nevertheless, the ultimate source of the nation's wealth.</p>
<p>You can't guillotine "the markets" but someone has to question seriously why this unelected aristocracy of financial whizzes gets to dictate to democracies around the world?</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64879872,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jjffmm&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64879872" title="Link to this comment">#7</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 5:23 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64884388"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64884388,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dcsessions&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;D. C. Sessions&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://dcsessions.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=DCSessions4F464B56-7189-A0BE-BB34-AFC6858536F2.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://dcsessions.newsvine.com/">D. C. Sessions</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64884388" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><blockquote>
<p>Mitt Romney has said he intends to dramatically scale back the federal role in helping students go to college.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>He knows from personal experience that it's not needed.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64884388,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dcsessions&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64884388" title="Link to this comment">#8</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 7:21 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64886567"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64886567,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;anitagehret&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;anita gehret&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://anitagehret.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://anitagehret.newsvine.com/">anita gehret</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64886567" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>i am sooo sick of hearing tha same old lie from republicans that giving more money to tha rich will create more jobs. they LIE! 12 years now they have been telling it. they have used this excuse to take money away from much needed programs such as this. they dare put our country in such a mess, and blame Obama for it plus obstruct his progress ON PURPOSE,  then cry that they can do a better job at fixing what THEY screwed up! TRICKLE DOWN ECONOMICS IS LIKE GETTING PISSED ON, SO, REPUBLICANS, PLEASE QUIT PISSING ON MY AMERICAN DREAM! GET OFF OF YOUR RICH LAZY BUTTS AND HELP OBAMA FIX THA MESS YOU ALL MADE. OR COME NOVEMBER, SOME REPUBLICAN HOUSE REPS AND SENATE  MEMBERS WILL BE ON THA UNEMPLOYMENT LINE! I'M WILLING TO RALLY OTHERS TO MAKE IT A REALITY!</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64886567,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;anitagehret&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64886567" title="Link to this comment">#9</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 8:37 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64886927"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64886927,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;anitagehret&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;anita gehret&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://anitagehret.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://anitagehret.newsvine.com/">anita gehret</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64886927" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>they better feel fortunate, if i had my way about it all, tha rich would be paying 40-45% in taxes, a high rate penalty on offshore accounts, id close all loopholes in tha tax system, outlaw lobbyists to pay off legislators, penalty of death for both offenders. and put a mandate that every canidate for federal public office has to spend 5 years on tha street as a homeless person, stripped of their wealth and influence. i know this sounds extreme, but they have lost too much touch with tha common american. i would also enforce strict regulations on corporate america, not allowing any monopolies and tax at 75% rate to those companies who move their buisnesses outside of tha USA. i would also slash tha pay of every top official in tha government. if they have wealth before office, we dont need to give them that much pay, after all, we need to keep THEM in tha REAL world.... OUR WORLD. I have other ideas, but i know ppl think they are too extreme.... but they would solve all our problems, dont you think? i do!</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64886927,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;anitagehret&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64886927" title="Link to this comment">#10</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 8:53 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64890398"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64890398,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;mattnichols&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;matt nichols&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://mattnichols.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://mattnichols.newsvine.com/">matt nichols</a></div></div><div id="commentText_64890398" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I'm not sure how many people know just the gravity of this situation. This is no joke. I like to occupy Gretawire, and after a year I have a pretty good sense of what is coming out of Fox, and just how effective their message is. I will go out on a limb and say 90% of that community have negative views of higher education. I am not exaggerating. Sometimes I feel like I am in a dream if I hang out there for too long. It's absolutely amazing.</p>
</p>
<p>That said, I have a dog in this fight. (oh man, they would have a field day over there at GW with that comment). My son is graduating high school this june and has been accepted at UC Santa Cruz. He will be the first of anyone in his family to go to college. This is attributed to his amazing character, and hard work throughout high school. I don't know how we are going to afford this, but I'm pretty sure it will have to include loans. I was appalled when I read about this story today. Granted, it is small in comparison to the entire issue of college tuition costs, but this is something tangible we can get our hands on right now. With knowing what I know now about how the GOP want to funnel money in certain directions, I am incredibly angry. Please help fight this with me. I found this petition. I don't know if it will help, but I must try to do something</p>
</p>
<p><a href="http://act.credoaction.com/campaign/reid_federal_student_loans/"><a href="http://act.credoaction.com/campaign/reid_federal_student_loans/">http://act.credoaction.com/campaign/reid_federal_student_loans/</a></a></p>
</p>
<p>You know, these public schools are no longer "public". I saw a report that the Universities are accepting way more out of state tuition, because those students pay so much more, and the schools need the money. My son applied to UC Davis and UC Berkeley as well. We knew he probably wouldn't get in to Berkeley because he doesn't have a 4.0, but we  (he especially) were hopeful about Davis. And I can't help but think if our economy was healthy he would of had a better chance to get in there. We are all so excited for him to go to Santa Cruz. I will work three jobs if I have to. Rachel, can you cover this some next week? I hear President Obama is going to start pushing on this next week at some Universities. We need all the help we can get. Thank you Rachel for all you do.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64890398,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;mattnichols&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64890398" title="Link to this comment">#11</a> - Fri Apr 20, 2012 10:45 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c64899340"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64899340,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-tiffanyhprescott&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Tiffany Hunter Prescott&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://fb-tiffanyhprescott.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=null0CD223EF-7F53-CAFF-CD90-FB00429C4B00.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://fb-tiffanyhprescott.newsvine.com/">Tiffany Hunter Prescott</a><span class="facebookVia">via Facebook</span></div></div><div id="commentText_64899340" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Two thoughts:</p>
<p>(1) If they could somehow extend the rate cut to mid-november (after the elections), I am pretty sure there would be bi-partisan support.  The republican party will do anything to ensure that this adminstration is not successful on fufilling any of its promises. </p>
<p>(2) Doesn't the republican party realize they are only increasing the amount of money that wil be necessary to bail out the banks and federal government when the student loan crisis hits?  But then again, I should pobably see my first point.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:64899340,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;11311001&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-tiffanyhprescott&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c64899340" title="Link to this comment">#12</a> - Sat Apr 21, 2012 8:22 AM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div></div><div class="commentcontainer"><div class="vine-p p-comment_CommentForm commentfields use_zinger"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;canLink&quot;:true,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3399606&quot;,&quot;isPrivate&quot;:false}"></div><a name="entercomment"></a><div class="commentbody"><div class="c_author"><div class="user"><a><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" />Leave a Comment:</a></div></div><div class="c_text"><div class="user"><div class="commentsForm-errors hide"></div><table class="commentform"><tr><td><div class="commentRegFormDiv"><form class="commentRegForm" method="POST" action="/_nv/api/accounts/register"><input type="hidden" name="responseType" value="json"><input type="hidden" name="postCommentGroupJoin" value=""><input type="hidden" name="postCommentGroupAccept" value=""><input type="hidden" name